  "doc_id": "43950",
  "text": "ach year in the United States, approximately 480,000 infants are born prematurely, representing 12% of live births [CITATION_1] . Mothers of newborn infants who are hospitalized in the neonatal intensive care unit (NICU) exhibit high rates of aversive emotional states, including clinically significant symptoms of depression and anxiety disorders [CITATION_2] ). These symptoms have been shown to affect both the mother's quality of life and her infant's development [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The prevalence of poor psychological well-being among NICU mothers highlights a critical role for NICU nurses: \"neonatal care providers have a unique relationship with mothers and a golden opportunity to identify symptoms and provide appropriate referrals and support\" (Beck, 2003, p. 37) .",
